<p><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>¬†</mtext><mspace linebreak="newline"></mspace></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> ~ \\ </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height:0em;vertical-align:0em;"></span><span class="mspace nobreak">¬†</span></span><span class="mspace newline"></span></span></span></span></p>

<p>Finally, since we know that $z_h^{&lt;t&gt;} = W_{hx} x^{&lt;t&gt;} + W_{hh} h^{&lt;t-1&gt;} + b_h$, we can finish BTT by finding the derivative of loss function with respect to $W_{hx}$, $W_{hh}$ and $b_h$.</p>

<p>Let‚Äôs start with derivative of loss function with respect to $W_{hx}$:</p>

<p><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><menclose notation="box"><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="false"><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msub><mi>W</mi><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msubsup><mi>z</mi><mi>h</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mfrac><mo>‚ãÖ</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msubsup><mi>z</mi><mi>h</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msubsup></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msub><mi>W</mi><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msubsup><mi>z</mi><mi>h</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mfrac><mo>‚ãÖ</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mi>h</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>‚àí</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>b</mi><mi>h</mi></msub><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msub><mi>W</mi><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">‚àÇ</mi><msubsup><mi>z</mi><mi>h</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mfrac><mo>‚ãÖ</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></mstyle></mstyle></menclose></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 
\boxed{\frac{‚àÇ L^{&lt;t&gt;}}{‚àÇ W_{hx}} = \frac{‚àÇ L^{&lt;t&gt;}}{‚àÇ z_h^{&lt;t&gt;}} \cdot \frac{‚àÇ z_h^{&lt;t&gt;}}{‚àÇ W_{hx}} = \frac{‚àÇ L^{&lt;t&gt;}}{‚àÇ z_h^{&lt;t&gt;}} \cdot \frac{‚àÇ (W_{hx} x^{&lt;t&gt;} + W_{hh} h^{&lt;t-1&gt;} + b_h)}{‚àÇ W_{hx}} = \frac{‚àÇ L^{&lt;t&gt;}}{‚àÇ z_h^{&lt;t&gt;}} \cdot x^{&lt;t&gt;}}
